---

<BaseLayout
  title="6-Day Northern Tanzania Safari | Go Kilimanjaro Treks"
  description="Six-day northern Tanzania safari across the major parks."
  schemas={schemas}
>
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="page-hero-eyebrow">Tanzania Safari Itinerary</span>
    <h1>6-Day Northern Tanzania Safari.</h1>
    <p>Six-day northern Tanzania safari across the major parks.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Request a Quote &#x2192;</a>
      <a href="https://wa.me/255677917500" class="btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&#x1F4AC; WhatsApp Nelson</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">6 Days / 5 Nights Tanzania Classic Safari Discover the Untamed Beauty of Tanzania's Most Iconic Wildlife Destinations</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Starting From USD 2,150 Per Person Rates depend on season, accommodation category, and group size.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 1: Arrival in Tanzania - Welcome to Arusha</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Upon arrival at Kilimanjaro International Airport (JRO), you will be warmly welcomed by your professional safari guide and transferred to your accommodation in Arusha, the gateway to Tanzania's renowned northern safari circuit.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Surrounded by the green foothills of Mount Meru, Arusha offers a peaceful introduction to Tanzania's natural beauty. The remainder of the day is yours to relax and recover from your journey while preparing for the exciting wildlife adventure ahead.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: River Trees Inn</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: HB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 2: Tarangire National Park - Among Giants and Baobabs</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, depart for Tarangire National Park, one of Tanzania's most scenic wildlife areas, famous for its ancient baobab trees and impressive elephant populations.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">As you explore the park, encounter diverse wildlife including lions, giraffes, zebras, wildebeests, buffaloes, and a remarkable variety of birdlife. The Tarangire River serves as a permanent water source, attracting animals throughout the year and creating excellent game-viewing opportunities.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After a rewarding day in the wilderness, continue to your lodge for dinner and overnight.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Country Lodge Karatu</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 3: Central Serengeti - Into Africa's Endless Plains</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, journey toward the world-famous Serengeti National Park through the beautiful Ngorongoro Highlands, enjoying spectacular scenery along the way.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Upon entering the Serengeti, vast open plains stretch endlessly before you. Begin your game drive in Central Serengeti, one of the most wildlife-rich regions of the park and home to abundant predators and resident wildlife throughout the year.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Keep watch for lions resting beneath acacia trees, cheetahs scanning the horizon, leopards hidden among the woodlands, and large herds of grazers moving across the savannah.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Baobab Tented Camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 4: Southern Serengeti - Following Nature's Rhythm</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Today you venture into the Southern Serengeti, a region renowned for its sweeping grasslands and seasonal wildlife concentrations.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This area plays an important role in the annual migration cycle and offers exceptional opportunities to observe large herds of wildebeests, zebras, gazelles, and the predators that follow them. The open plains provide breathtaking scenery and unforgettable wildlife encounters in one of Africa's most iconic landscapes.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Spend the day exploring this remarkable wilderness before returning to camp for a relaxing evening under the African sky.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Baobab Tented Camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 5: Ngorongoro Crater - A World Within a Crater</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, depart Serengeti and travel to the Ngorongoro Conservation Area, home to one of the most extraordinary wildlife destinations on earth.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Descend into the Ngorongoro Crater, a vast volcanic caldera teeming with wildlife. Within its natural walls lives an incredible concentration of animals including lions, elephants, buffaloes, hippos, hyenas, and the endangered black rhino.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a picnic lunch on the crater floor surrounded by spectacular scenery before ascending to the rim and continuing to your lodge for your final evening in Tanzania's safari country.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Manyara Best View Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Day 6: Departure - Farewell to Tanzania</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy breakfast while taking in the beautiful highland views before beginning your journey back to Arusha.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Depending on your flight schedule, a short stop for shopping or local experiences may be arranged before your transfer to Kilimanjaro International Airport (JRO) for departure.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">As your safari concludes, you leave Tanzania with unforgettable memories of magnificent wildlife, breathtaking landscapes, and the timeless spirit of Africa.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: BB</p>
  </div>
</section>

